de grounds and finally to Jordan s Point where a shuttle will run guests from that lot to Marshall Hall  WE KINDLY ASK THAT PARTICIPANTS CARPOOL WHENEVER POSSIBLE  We are expecting about 300 participants to this year s STEM conference   With extensive renovations happening around post and in downtown Lexington  we are asking everyone to carpool wherever and whenever possible to minize the potential impact   Below are convenient links to help you with driving directions and available parking locations   We will also have signage around post as well as parking attendants at the start of each day to assist you   Read below for more details  Find us on Google Maps  click here or on map image  Marshall Hall  VMI  Lexington  VA 24450 VMI  on post  Parking On Post Parking is reserved for this conference beside the Center for Leadership and Ethics as your primary parking lot location  It contains 87 spaces  see map below  building location 23 and pink parking lot just above  On Tuesday from 7 00 a m  until 9 30 a m  we will have parking attendants available to assist and direct traffic  On Wednesday  they will be available from 7 30 a m  until 9 30 a m  Weather permitting  we will have overflow parking available on the Parade Grounds  large green field  center of map  For inclement weather circumstance  cars will be routed to Jordan s Point Parking Lot which is past the CLE parking lot and will be marked with signage   See location 43 on the map  the color coded parking lot to the right  All other parking locations are available on a first come  first served basis  Please refer to this map to locate other available on post parking lots  Printable on post map  click here or on map  VMI Post Map Lexington Parking Information   Maps Downtown parking and information Courthouse parking deck and Randolph Street Parking Lot  More than 150 free parking spaces are available in these two lots that are located on Varner Lane across from the Lexington Visitors Center and just a short w